translations.name: Naineri Amanab New Testament
translations.description: The New Testament in Amanab – Amanab is spoken by about 11,000 people on and around the border between Indoneisa and Papua New Guinea. Naineri is one of its many dialects. A staggering 93% of Amanab speakers are Christians, with 24% of those being Evangelical. It was for these believers that Wycliffe Bible Translators made an Amanab New Testament available in 2001.
